title: Łozy, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship
data: Łozy [ˈwɔzɨ] is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Płoskinia, within Braniewo County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland.[1] It lies approximately 8 kilometres (5 mi) south of Płoskinia, 23 km (14 mi) south-east of Braniewo, and 58 km (36 mi) north-west of the regional capital Olsztyn. Before 1772 the area was part of Kingdom of Poland, and in 1772–1945 it belonged to Prussia and Germany (East Prussia). This Braniewo County location article is a stub.
